Santos Aviation Limited, providers of maintenance and interior refurbishing services for government and privately owned aircraft, has concluded plans to host the first Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) of the United States repair station in the country. General Manager of Santos Aviation, Engineer Segun Adesanya, said the company will be hosting a diamond-studded launch featuring FAA part 145 repair station. According to Adesanya, the event, which will be on February 24, 2022, will feature a keynote address by Capt. Hans Kraus. He explained that his agents and employees have professional and technical licenses from the FAA of the United States to provide services on America made and American registered aircraft. He disclosed that services provided by Santos include aircraft/airline seat covers upgrade, carpet binding and surging, galleys, lavatory, panels and PSU, refurbishing and sewing services.